Concepts of stress. General and specific reactions to environmental stress, oxidative stress. Abiotic and biotic stress factors and their mechanisms. Low and high temperature, water excess and deficiency, soil acidity, shortage and excess of minerals and light, salinity.  Influence of UV-radiation and radioactive exposure. Distribution, types and mechanisms of contaminants, influence of global changes, influence of herbivores, bacteria and viruses, influence of competition conditions at different levels of organization (cell, organism, community).Objectives/eesmärkid:  To explain the general and specific reactions of plants to unfavourable environmental conditions. To learn, how to evaluate the physiological status of plants by external symtoms of stress. To analyse a scientific article, (make a presentation about the effects of one certain stress factor).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The Student knows the generral and more specific reactions of plants to unfavorable environmental conditions, is able to assess the physiological condition of a plant by external view, is able to analyze a scientific article.
